we have a situation where we have oc installed on a windows iis box (4.5 was running ok) using a mysql backend.  we have now deployed oc 5 ee to the machine and are directing it to sql server.  the first run wizard seems to complete ok and the database is created, the issue is after the setup completes it bring the user to the login page and they are not able to login as the admin... it spins for a while then fails.  the following logs entries are generated (see below) we have set the permissions on the temp directory and i have verified that the php.ini file has not changed (still points at windows temp).  any thoughts?

